[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is 3 179 195, with reports of cases by 214 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.4% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with over 1 million confirmed cases now represents 33.5% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 220 685 deaths have been reported, 216 052 (97.9%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by France, the UK, Germany, Turkey, Russia, Iran, and China as number 10. - Mod.UBA]

